JobDescription:
scope & prioritize data requirements, design intelligent dashboard & systems alerts, connect and collaborate with business & tech teams 
gather data improvement initiatives across sales systems teams, regional operations teams, product teams, and the IT engineering team; 
build pre work data standard templates to be used across various sales systems projects to gather data requirements; 
ensure and supervise business value creation for the data governance program 
apply data governance frameworks and standard methodologies, practices, and processes to the data assets 
implement the data governance operating model that includes designing Data Governance organization, roles and responsibilities, and success metrics 
Four plus years of experience working in consulting, sales operations, or program management 
At least two years of work experience in strategy through execution data governance or data quality project 
Understanding and experience with one or more of the following or equivalent data governance and data quality technologies - Informatica AXON, Collibra; 
Designing and developing Data Governance technology solutions that includes data dictionary & business glossaries, data standards and policies; data lineage and catalogs; 
Creating detailed documentation related to Data Governance processes and policies; 
Having familiarity with compliance areas is a plus for e.g. Contracts Management, Product and Asset Management, CCPA, GDPR regulations and building compliance processes; 
Understanding of SFDC data architecture and data integration patterns, identifying and prioritizing critical data elements across SFDC objects, Data Quality Processes and important metrics, metadata management; 
Understanding of enterprise data concepts such as Master Data Management and Enterprise Data Warehouse, experience with MDM standards; 
Understanding or knowledge of SQL, build DG metrics visualization using tools such as Tableau or Power BI 
Familiarity with Salesforce concepts such as CPQ, Docusign CLM 
Train teams on foundational processes and activities to bring data under governance 
Experience with process documentation 
Ability to communicate efficiently with different internal partners with clarity 
Understanding of complex data hierarchies and relationships for e.g. account and opportunity hierarchies, legal entity structures etc.

