Analyze and integrate Omics data including single cell transcriptomics and epigenomics to advance disease biology while understanding and targeting identification in lung and inflammatory diseases; 
Apply the findings of target identification studies in the area of lung and inflammatory diseases to identify new mechanisms, pathways and finally druggable targets for the development of novel, causative therapies; 
Apply statistical and machine learning methods to patient biobank data to understand disease drivers across patient cohorts; 
Evaluate lung portfolio projects using data driven approaches and work with our strategic partners to drive the process of drug development for validated mechanisms; 
Plan and execute studies together with lab heads and the portfolio project lead to validate and understand the biology of identified targets and new mechanisms; 
Collaborate and communicate effectively with data science teams on data analysis and integration projects, lung portfolio project tasks and data driven activities within the collaboration; 
Drive continuous improvement in methodology, processes and formats through own expertise and experience in collaboration with data science groups; 
Participate in scientific meetings, seminars and represent the strategic collaboration at internal and external meetings and conferences; 
Perform other related responsibilities as necessitated by the position. 
Doctorate or Doctor of Philosophy (PhD) in natural sciences (genetics, molecular biology, immunology), or medical science with a quantitative or computational component; 
Proven track record of successful scientific working, such as a post-doctoral fellowship or successful funding applications or a strong publication record; 
Maintain strong experience with a common programming language for data analysis such as R or Python; 
Knowledge of machine learning methods for data integration; 
Demonstrate the ability to work in a team environment and the ability to adapt to the atmosphere of a dynamic research organization; 
Able to communicate and interact with interdisciplinary project teams; 
Maintain creative and flexible thinking, being open minded and challenging the status quo; 
Able and willing to think outside the box to develop and adopt relevant emerging technologies; 
Able to build excellent working relationships, to initiate new collaborative projects and to take a hands on approach for collaborative scientific discovery efforts; 
Sustain excellent written and oral communication skills. 
Familiar with Bash, Structured Query Language (SQL) and prior experience with high performance and cloud computing; 
Knowledge of computational biology and experience in computational pipelines for analysis of large datasets, such as single cell genomics, transcriptomics and epigenomics; 
Uphold experience with other Omics data modalities and genetics; 
Solid background in fibrotic or inflammatory diseases and lung diseases; 
Continue experience with cellular and/or animal modeling of lung or inflammatory disease biology.

Define, track, and manage key performance metrics and insights across teams, programs, and business units. Provide metrics and reporting that drive key decisions and actions from business partners and leaders. Design, implementation, and maintenance of ETL pipelines to combine data sources and prep them for analysis. Collaborate with various departments like Finance, Sales, Marketing, and Product to help incorporate the insights derived from the data to facilitate a data-driven culture across the organization. Develop interactive and effective dashboards that communicate business performance and insights. Experience working with structured and unstructured data analysis, developing visualizations, and producing reports from multiple data sources Highly proficient in SQL and BI reporting and visualization tools (SQL, Alteryx, Tableau) Some scripting knowledge or willingness to learn (python preferred) Strong analytical and problem-solving skills Excellent communicator, both written and verbal 
